WEBVTT

00:01.500 --> 00:02.667
<i>PREVIOUSLY</i>
<i>ON "RED BAND SOCIETY"...</i>

00:02.750 --> 00:04.333
WHAT ARE YOU IN FOR?
BUNK LIVER.

00:04.417 --> 00:06.250
DOCTORS GAVE ME SIX WEEKS, TOPS,
BEFORE IT CRAPS OUT.

00:06.333 --> 00:08.375
ARE YOU SCARED OF ME?
AS IF I'D BE
SCARED OF A GIMP.

00:09.500 --> 00:11.250
OH!
LEO!

00:11.333 --> 00:12.959
SO, WHAT DO YOU WANT TO DO?
I WANT TO DO THIS.

00:14.333 --> 00:15.917
Jordi: ALL RIGHT?
I'M SICK OF THEM.

00:16.000 --> 00:17.417
I'M SICK OF THIS PLACE.
I'M SICK OF BEING SICK.

00:17.500 --> 00:19.458
EVERYONE NEEDS A FRIEND,
RIGHT?

00:20.166 --> 00:21.667
DOES THAT ANSWER
YOUR QUESTION?

00:21.750 --> 00:23.458
I'M GONNA NEED A RUSH
ON CHARLIE HUTCHISON.

00:23.542 --> 00:25.458
HE'S BEING TRANSFERRED
TO CONVALESCENT CARE,

00:25.542 --> 00:28.250
I HAD TO REPORT YOU FOR
FALSIFYING CHARLIE'S LAB WORK.

00:28.333 --> 00:31.500
HOW DID --
I KNEW YOU WANTED TO
BUY CHARLIE MORE TIME.

00:31.583 --> 00:32.625
YOU'RE SUSPENDED.

00:37.542 --> 00:39.542
[ MANNEQUIN MEN'S
"ENOUGH" PLAYS ]

00:41.542 --> 00:43.500
Charlie: <i>ARISTOTLE SAID</i>

00:43.583 --> 00:45.959
<i>THAT KNOWING YOURSELF</i>
<i>IS THE BEGINNING OF WISDOM.</i>

00:48.792 --> 00:52.208
<i>HERE AT OCEAN PARK, WHILE WE'RE</i>
<i>BUSY GETTING TO KNOW OURSELVES,</i>

00:52.291 --> 00:53.834
<i>WE COUNT ON NURSE JACKSON</i>

00:53.917 --> 00:56.041
<i>TO KNOW ALL THE OTHER STUFF</i>
<i>FOR US...</i>

00:56.125 --> 00:58.709
♪ BUT NEVER FEEL
THE WAY I WANT ♪
[ CELLPHONE BEEPING ]

00:58.792 --> 01:02.041
<i>...LIKE WHEN DASH HAS HIS FIRST</i>
<i>OXYGEN TREATMENT OF THE DAY...</i>

01:02.125 --> 01:07.542
♪ THINGS WORTH SEEING,
BUT NEVER SEE WHAT I WANT ♪

01:07.625 --> 01:11.709
♪ AND TIME'S TOUGH, TIME'S HARD,
TIME'S BETTER ♪
[ CHUCKLES ]

01:11.792 --> 01:14.083
♪ BUT TIME IS NOT ENOUGH ♪

01:14.166 --> 01:16.750
<i>...OR HOW TO REIN IN LEO WHEN</i>
<i>HE GETS A LITTLE INSENSITIVE...</i>

01:16.834 --> 01:18.750
♪ TIME'S HARD, TIME'S TOUGH,
TIME'S BETTER ♪

01:18.834 --> 01:20.750
<i>...ESPECIALLY</i>
<i>WHEN HIS NEW LOVE LIFE...</i>

01:20.834 --> 01:22.959
♪ BUT TIME IS NOT ENOUGH ♪
<i>...IS AFFECTING HIS ROOMMATE...</i>

01:23.041 --> 01:25.208
<i>OR THAT DR. McANDREW</i>
<i>GETS SUPER CRANKY</i>

01:25.291 --> 01:28.542
<i>IF HE DOESN'T GET HIS AFTERNOON</i>
<i>FIX FROM THE TACO TRUCK.</i>

01:28.625 --> 01:30.458
<i>HOLA.</i>

01:30.542 --> 01:35.166
<i>FOR ME, THOUGH, I GUESS</i>
<i>IT DOESN'T MATTER VERY MUCH.</i>

01:35.250 --> 01:39.208
<i>I JUST LIKE IT BETTER</i>
<i>WHEN SHE'S HERE.</i>

01:39.291 --> 01:41.709
MMM. KIMCHI.

01:41.792 --> 01:44.542
TASTES JUST LIKE FEET --
SPICY, DELICIOUS FEET.

01:44.625 --> 01:45.917
[ CHUCKLES ]

01:46.000 --> 01:47.542
DO YOU THINK
I HAVE A FOOT FETISH?

01:47.625 --> 01:49.959
BRITTANY, IN THE THREE DAYS
SINCE JACKSON'S BEEN GONE,

01:50.041 --> 01:51.542
I'VE WORKED FOUR DOUBLES,

01:51.625 --> 01:53.709
WHICH I DIDN'T EVEN KNOW
WAS MATHEMATICALLY POSSIBLE.

01:53.792 --> 01:55.291
I'VE BEEN THROWN UP
ON 11 TIMES,

01:55.375 --> 01:56.875
SHAVED A SCREAMING CHILD

01:56.959 --> 01:58.250
WHOSE MEDICATION WAS MAKING HIM
GROW BODY HAIR,

01:58.333 --> 01:59.709
AND NOW
I'M COMPULSIVELY EATING

01:59.792 --> 02:01.375
DEEP-FRIED BEEF
JUST TO STAY AWAKE.

02:01.458 --> 02:03.041
YOU GOT QUESTIONS
ABOUT YOUR KINKY SIDE?

02:03.125 --> 02:04.500
TAKE IT UP
WITH YOUR THERAPIST.

02:06.208 --> 02:08.625
YES! TACO DAY.

02:08.709 --> 02:14.000
I'VE BEEN THINKING ABOUT THIS
THROUGHOUT MY WHOLE APPENDECT...

02:16.959 --> 02:19.875
SERIOUSLY? NOBODY COULD HAVE
GRABBED ME AN EXTRA TACO?

02:19.959 --> 02:22.166
WELL, TECHNICALLY,
SOMEBODY <i>COULD</i> HAVE,

02:22.250 --> 02:24.041
BUT FETCHING TACOS
FOR DOCTORS

02:24.125 --> 02:25.667
ISN'T REALLY PART
OF BEING A NURSE.

02:25.750 --> 02:27.041
IT'S MORE OF A THING
THAT FRIENDS DO.

02:27.125 --> 02:28.333
AND SINCE YOU FIRED
YOUR FRIEND --

02:28.417 --> 02:30.166
SUSPENDED, NOT FIRED.

02:30.250 --> 02:32.667
PENDING REVIEW,
LIKE YOUR TACO DELIVERY.

02:32.750 --> 02:35.959
YOU KNOW, THE TRUCK'S STILL
OUT THERE. I COULD RUN OUT...

02:36.041 --> 02:38.834
AND BE ON ENEMA DUTY
FOR THE REST OF THE MONTH.

02:38.917 --> 02:43.500
OKAY. OKAY.
I SEE HOW THIS IS.

02:43.583 --> 02:46.458
NOTHING GETS PAST YOU.

02:46.542 --> 02:49.000
I'M SORRY. I'M JUST NOT GOOD
AT TAKING SIDES.

02:49.083 --> 02:51.291
ESPECIALLY WHEN ONE OF THE SIDES
HAS GEORGE CLOONEY HAIR

02:51.375 --> 02:52.917
AND COULD FATHER
MY FUTURE CHILDREN.

02:54.375 --> 02:56.458
I JUST FEEL TERRIBLE
FOR NURSE JACKSON. I DO.

02:56.542 --> 02:58.458
BUT I JUST KEEP PICTURING HER
SITTING ALONE

02:58.542 --> 03:01.458
IN HER SAD, LITTLE APARTMENT,
FEEDING HER CATS,

03:01.542 --> 03:04.000
HEATING SINGLE-PORTION MICROWAVE
DINNERS BEFORE SITTING DOWN

03:04.083 --> 03:06.458
TO WATCH 17 CONSECUTIVE EPISODES
OF "MURDER, SHE WROTE."

03:06.542 --> 03:09.125
YOU PAINT
QUITE A PICTURE.

03:09.208 --> 03:12.083
BUT WHAT DO YOU KNOW ABOUT
NURSE JACKSON'S <i>ACTUAL</i> LIFE?

03:12.166 --> 03:14.875
UM...NOTHING.

03:18.417 --> 03:20.333
<i>I DON'T KNOW ABOUT YOU,</i>

03:20.417 --> 03:24.000
<i>BUT I'M NOT FEELING</i>
<i>ANGELA LANSBURY IN HERE.</i>

03:24.083 --> 03:26.333
MMM!
SMELLS LIKE PARIS IN HERE.

03:26.417 --> 03:30.417
GOUGèRES, COQ AU VIN,
AND FOR DESSERT, CRèME BRûLéE.

03:30.500 --> 03:32.250
IT LOOKS AMAZING, AUNT DENA.
WHAT'S THE OCCASION?

03:32.333 --> 03:34.417
MY FAVORITE NIECE
VISITING FROM COLLEGE.

03:34.500 --> 03:36.375
I'D SAY THAT'S
A PRETTY BIG OCCASION.

03:36.458 --> 03:37.834
I'M YOUR <i>ONLY</i> NIECE.

03:37.917 --> 03:40.333
BUT STILL MY FAVORITE.
IT'S JUST A SMALL POOL.

03:40.417 --> 03:42.500
[ CHUCKLES ]
BESIDES, IT'S NOT LIKE

03:42.583 --> 03:44.709
I HAVE ANYTHING ELSE
TO DO RIGHT NOW,

03:44.792 --> 03:47.959
AND COOKING
JUST KEEPS ME SANE.

03:48.041 --> 03:49.333
I STILL CAN'T BELIEVE
THEY SUSPENDED YOU.

03:49.417 --> 03:52.166
WELCOME TO THE MODERN
MEDICAL BUREAUCRACY,

03:52.250 --> 03:54.500
WHERE THE ONLY THING
THAT MATTERS

03:54.583 --> 03:57.667
IS PAPERWORK AND PROTOCOL.

03:57.750 --> 04:00.667
PENCIL-PUSHING PINHEADS.

04:00.750 --> 04:02.125
DO YOU THINK THEY COULD
FIRE YOU FOR THIS?

04:02.208 --> 04:04.166
IF I GET FIRED
FOR DOING THE RIGHT THING --

04:04.250 --> 04:06.792
HONESTLY,
I SHOULD JUST WALK AWAY.

04:06.875 --> 04:08.792
WOULD YOU?

04:08.875 --> 04:11.709
NOW, YOU KNOW NYU's
NOT GONNA PAY FOR ITSELF.

04:11.792 --> 04:13.333
[ SCOFFS ]
DAD CAN COVER IT.

04:13.417 --> 04:15.667
YOUR DAD COVERS TUITION.
I COVER ROOM AND BOARD,

04:15.750 --> 04:17.333
NOT TO MENTION
ALL THOSE PEA COATS

04:17.417 --> 04:19.834
AND FANCY COCKTAILS
YOU'RE TOO YOUNG TO DRINK.

04:19.917 --> 04:20.959
SO I'LL GET A JOB.

04:21.041 --> 04:22.375
[ LAUGHS ]
SERIOUSLY!

04:22.458 --> 04:24.959
I DON'T WANT YOU
STAYING SOMEPLACE

04:25.041 --> 04:26.959
THAT'S MAKING YOU MISERABLE
JUST SO I CAN HAVE

04:27.041 --> 04:28.709
THE DELUXE MEAL PLAN
IN THE DINING HALL.

04:28.792 --> 04:30.625
YOU'VE ALREADY GIVEN UP SO MUCH
BECAUSE OF ME.

04:30.709 --> 04:32.125
DON'T START WITH THAT.

04:32.208 --> 04:33.709
I'M JUST SAYING,

04:33.792 --> 04:36.500
MAYBE THE SUSPENSION HAPPENED
FOR A REASON.

04:36.583 --> 04:38.291
MAYBE THIS IS YOUR CHANCE

04:38.375 --> 04:41.291
TO GO BACK TO WHAT
YOU'RE SUPPOSED TO DO.

04:41.375 --> 04:42.959
YOU HAVE A GIFT.

04:46.208 --> 04:47.834
[ TYPING ]

04:47.917 --> 04:49.959
[ CELLPHONE CHIMES ]
YOU'RE LATE.

04:50.041 --> 04:51.792
THAT'S WHAT I SAID TO MY PERIOD
LAST MONTH.

04:51.875 --> 04:53.875
LOOK, ME AND LEO SET UP
THIS WHOLE GET-TOGETHER

04:53.959 --> 04:55.875
BECAUSE
WE NEED TO DO SOMETHING

04:55.959 --> 04:58.291
ABOUT THIS NURSE JACKSON
SITUATION.
RIGHT, THE WAY WE SEE IT,

04:58.375 --> 05:00.291
WE'VE GOT VARIOUS METHODS
AT OUR DISPOSAL.

05:00.375 --> 05:03.458
SIT-INS, UH, PICKET LINES,
HUNGER STRIKES.

05:03.542 --> 05:05.417
EMMA, I THINK
WE FOUND YOUR CALLING.

05:05.500 --> 05:08.083
[ CELLPHONE CHIMES ]
BUT, UM,
WE THINK OUR BEST OPTION

05:08.166 --> 05:09.875
IS TO WRITE A LETTER
TO THE POWERS THAT BE

05:09.959 --> 05:12.083
DEMANDING THAT THEY BRING
NURSE JACKSON BACK IMMEDIATELY.

05:12.166 --> 05:14.917
Kara: IT'S ADORABLE
THAT YOU GUYS ARE GETTING

05:15.000 --> 05:16.333
ALL CIVIL RIGHTS-Y
ABOUT THIS,

05:16.417 --> 05:18.750
BUT I SLEPT TILL 9:00 A.M.
THIS MORNING,

05:18.834 --> 05:21.750
AND IT'S BEEN 24 HOURS SINCE
SOMEONE WATCHED ME PEE IN A CUP.

05:21.834 --> 05:23.709
ISN'T IT KIND OF BETTER
WITHOUT HER HERE?

05:23.792 --> 05:26.500
[ CELLPHONE CHIMES ]
LOOK, NURSE JACKSON
GOT SUSPENDED

05:26.583 --> 05:28.500
BECAUSE OF WHAT SHE DID
FOR CHARLIE.

05:28.583 --> 05:30.583
SHE WENT DOWN FIGHTING
FOR ONE OF US.

05:30.667 --> 05:34.458
SO, "TO THE POWERS
THAT BE..."

05:34.542 --> 05:36.667
"TO WHOM IT MAY CONCERN."
IT'S MORE OFFICIAL.

05:36.750 --> 05:39.166
AND RAISES
A FASCINATING QUESTION.

05:39.250 --> 05:41.041
WHO DOES IT CONCERN?

05:42.041 --> 05:44.000
THINK ABOUT IT.

05:44.083 --> 05:47.000
THERE ARE MILLIONS OF HOSPITALS
ALL OVER THE WORLD.

05:47.083 --> 05:48.834
SOMEHOW THEY ALL MANAGE
TO FUNCTION

05:48.917 --> 05:51.000
WITHOUT YOUR PRECIOUS
NURSE JACKSON.

05:51.083 --> 05:53.500
YOU THINK SHE'S LOSING SLEEP
OVER YOU?

05:53.583 --> 05:55.500
HE'S GOT A POINT.

05:55.583 --> 05:58.166
I'M SORRY. UH,
WE HAVEN'T REALLY MET YET.

05:58.250 --> 05:59.917
WHAT WAS YOUR NAME,
AGAIN?

06:00.000 --> 06:01.333
IT'S HUNTER.

06:01.417 --> 06:04.333
OKAY, I'M LEO.
NICE TO MEET YOU, HUNTER.

06:04.417 --> 06:06.291
AND SINCE
YOU'RE NEW AROUND HERE...

06:06.375 --> 06:07.750
[ CELLPHONE CHIMES ]
...I THINK
MAYBE YOU SHOULD, UM...

06:07.834 --> 06:11.166
[ CELLPHONE CHIMES ]
UH...MAYBE, UH...

06:11.250 --> 06:12.917
[ CELLPHONE CHIMES ]
MAYBE WHAT?

06:13.000 --> 06:14.583
NURSE JACKSON --
LEO, MAN,
JUST GET OFF THE PHONE.

06:14.667 --> 06:16.500
RIGHT, YEAH, MY BAD.
IT'S JUST, UH...

06:16.583 --> 06:18.208
MY FRIENDS JAY AND LAUREN,
THEY'RE LIKE FIVE MINUTES AWAY.

06:18.291 --> 06:20.208
I HAD NO IDEA
THEY WERE COMING.

06:20.291 --> 06:22.750
MAYBE THEY CAME TO BURN THEIR
BRAS IN HONOR OF NURSE JACKSON.

06:22.834 --> 06:24.750
[ SNICKERS ]
LOOK, WE, UH --
WE GOT TO GO.

06:24.834 --> 06:28.166
WE'LL BE BACK IN,
UM, AN HOUR, TWO TOPS.

06:28.250 --> 06:29.583
SERIOUSLY?

06:31.959 --> 06:33.166
DON'T LET THIS GUY
PULL YOU OFF-TRACK, MAN.

06:33.250 --> 06:35.500
YOU -- YOU GOT THIS.

06:35.583 --> 06:37.625
[ SCOFFS ]

06:38.625 --> 06:40.333
I WANT TO
KNOW EVERYTHING.

06:40.417 --> 06:41.834
DO THEY PUT A TIE ON THE DOOR,
LIKE, WHEN THEY'RE DOING IT?

06:41.917 --> 06:43.375
AND ISN'T LEO AFRAID

06:43.458 --> 06:45.083
HE'S GONNA IMPALE HIMSELF
ON HER CLAVICLE?

06:45.166 --> 06:47.500
THIS IS <i>SERIOUSLY</i>
HOW YOU GUYS SPEND YOUR TIME --

06:47.583 --> 06:49.041
GOSSIPING
ABOUT WHO'S KISSING WHO

06:49.125 --> 06:50.917
AND CRYING OVER
HOW NURSE WHAT'S-HER-FACE

06:51.000 --> 06:52.500
GOT HER PARKING SPACE
TAKEN AWAY?

06:52.583 --> 06:53.834
UM, I'M PRETTY SURE

06:53.917 --> 06:55.542
THEY DON'T WASTE
PARKING SPOTS ON NURSES.

06:55.625 --> 06:57.166
LOOK WHERE WE ARE.

06:57.250 --> 06:59.542
HOW CAN YOU STILL THINK
ANY OF THAT STUFF MATTERS?

07:00.709 --> 07:03.625
SO, WHAT <i>DOES</i> MATTER?
WHY ARE YOU
LISTENING TO HIM?

07:03.709 --> 07:05.125
YOU WANT TO FIND OUT?

07:05.208 --> 07:08.333
♪ OH, OH-HEY, OH ♪

07:08.417 --> 07:13.333
♪ OH, OH-HEY, OH ♪
COME WITH ME.
I'LL SHOW YOU SOMETHING REAL.

07:13.417 --> 07:16.458
♪ I FEEL LIKE, I FEEL LIKE
NOTHING'S IMPOSSIBLE ♪

07:16.542 --> 07:19.458
WOW.
WELL, I'M SORRY,
BUT IF THERE'S EVEN A CHANCE

07:19.542 --> 07:22.458
THAT HE'S TAKING HIS CLOTHES
OFF, I HAVE TO BE THERE.
♪ OH, OH-HEY, OH ♪

07:22.542 --> 07:24.625
♪ OH, OH-HEY, OH ♪
<i>DON'T DO IT, DASH.</i>
<i>STAND YOUR GROUND.</i>

07:24.709 --> 07:26.500
<i>SAY NO TO PEER PRESSURE.</i>

07:26.583 --> 07:29.000
♪ I FEEL LIKE, I FEEL LIKE ♪
<i>OR, YOU KNOW, DON'T.</i>

07:29.083 --> 07:33.792
♪ NOTHING'S IMPOSSIBLE ♪

07:34.875 --> 07:38.125
<i>LEO AND EMMA ARE ABOUT TO GO</i>
<i>ON THEIR FIRST OFFICIAL DATE.</i>

07:38.208 --> 07:39.500
<i>SEEMS LIKE A STEP</i>
<i>IN THE RIGHT DIRECTION.</i>

07:39.583 --> 07:41.083
AND I CAN'T WAIT
FOR YOU TO MEET JAY.

07:41.166 --> 07:44.125
WE'VE BEEN BEST FRIENDS
SINCE KINDERGARTEN.

07:44.208 --> 07:45.333
<i>SO WHY DOES EMMA LOOK LIKE SHE</i>
<i>WANTS TO TAKE TWO STEPS BACK?</i>
BOTH MADE VARSITY SOCCER
FRESHMAN YEAR.

07:45.417 --> 07:46.834
TEAM CO-CAPTAINS,
EVERYTHING.

07:46.917 --> 07:48.125
MAYBE YOU GUYS
SHOULD CATCH UP ON YOUR OWN.

07:48.208 --> 07:49.750
I CAN MEET THEM
ANOTHER TIME.

07:49.834 --> 07:51.834
NO. LOOK, I KNOW YOU'RE WORRIED
ABOUT MY FRIENDS,

07:51.917 --> 07:54.375
BUT I'VE TOLD THEM ABOUT YOU,
AND THEY'RE DYING TO MEET YOU.

07:54.458 --> 07:55.709
YOU TOLD THEM ABOUT ME?

07:55.792 --> 07:58.375
YEAH. YEAH, I DID.

07:58.458 --> 08:00.542
[ P.A. BEEPS ]

08:00.625 --> 08:05.250
OHH! LOOK AT UNCLE FESTER
GETTING SOME!

08:05.333 --> 08:08.041
[ LAUGHS ]
GOOD TO SEE YOU, MAN.

08:08.125 --> 08:10.208
YOU TOO, BUDDY.
OH!

08:10.291 --> 08:12.375
HOW'S THE LEG?
GONE, BUT NOT FORGOTTEN.

08:12.458 --> 08:13.709
LIKE MY YOUTH. HI.

08:13.792 --> 08:14.834
HI.
[ LAUGHS ]

08:14.917 --> 08:17.083
I'M DRAMATIC.N.

08:17.166 --> 08:19.583
GUYS, THIS IS EMMA,
MY GIRLFRIEND.

08:21.125 --> 08:22.875
NICE TO MEET YOU.
ALL RIGHT.
LET'S GO, PEOPLE.

08:22.959 --> 08:25.375
WE'VE BEEN IN THE CAR FOR ALMOST
THREE HOURS. I'M STARVING.

08:25.458 --> 08:27.041
WAIT.
WE'RE GOING TO LUNCH?

08:27.125 --> 08:29.041
HEY, I'M SORRY.
I DIDN'T...THINK.

08:29.125 --> 08:30.375
YOU STILL WANT TO COME?

08:30.458 --> 08:32.291
OF COURSE.

08:34.792 --> 08:37.542
Dash: LOOK, MAN,
THIS TOUR OF LINOLEUM IS COOL,

08:37.625 --> 08:39.417
BUT YOU KNOW
WHAT WOULD BE EVEN BETTER?

08:39.500 --> 08:42.125
PUTTING THE PEN TO THE PAPER,
SAVING A COMMUNITY WORKER'S JOB.

08:42.208 --> 08:44.083
LET'S GET NURSE JACKSON BACK
IN THE HOUSE, Y'ALL.

08:44.166 --> 08:46.667
WELL, WHY DON'T YOU JUST WAIT
FOR LEO TO WRITE THE LETTER?

08:46.750 --> 08:48.000
IT'S NOT LIKE YOU REALLY WANT
OUR INPUT ANYWAY.

08:48.083 --> 08:49.875
THAT'S NOT TRUE.
Jordi: YEAH, IT IS.

08:49.959 --> 08:51.333
DASH IS OBSESSED
WITH LEO.

08:51.417 --> 08:53.291
HE'S PRACTICALLY A GROUPIE.
IS THAT RIGHT?

08:53.375 --> 08:55.458
[ SIGHS ] FIRST OF ALL,
IT'S CALLED BEING A GOOD FRIEND,

08:55.542 --> 08:57.333
HAVING EACH OTHER'S BACKS.
[ ELEVATOR BELL DINGS ]

08:57.417 --> 08:59.750
RED BANDS IN THE FIRST PLACE.HE

08:59.834 --> 09:02.000
REALLY?
I GUESS THAT GUY IS A MEMBER.

09:02.083 --> 09:03.583
SO IS EVERYONE ELSE

09:03.667 --> 09:05.875
WHO EVER CAME
INTO THIS HOSPITAL FOR SURGERY.

09:05.959 --> 09:08.041
WOULD YOU THROW YOURSELF
INTO THE WHEELS OF AN AMBULANCE

09:08.125 --> 09:09.875
FOR ALL THEM, TOO?

09:09.959 --> 09:12.166
DEPENDS. ARE THEY
AS FULL OF CRAP AS YOU?

09:12.250 --> 09:15.917
WHY ARE WE FOLLOWING
MELLO YELLO?

09:16.000 --> 09:18.750
<i>MOCKING THE LIVER DISEASE --</i>
<i>WELL PLAYED.</i>

09:18.834 --> 09:20.250
HE'S NOT EVEN, LIKE,
TAKING US ANYWHERE.

09:20.333 --> 09:22.583
HE'S JUST WANDERING
THE DAMN HALL.

09:22.667 --> 09:25.166
EXCUSE ME, MA'AM.
I'M SO SORRY.

09:26.792 --> 09:28.500
YOU WERE SAYING?
[ LAUGHS ]

09:28.583 --> 09:31.375
<i>YOU HAVE TO ADMIT,</i>
<i>THAT WAS A LITTLE BIT COOL.</i>

09:31.458 --> 09:34.542
OOH! MNH-MNH.

09:34.625 --> 09:36.959
DISCARD.

09:37.041 --> 09:39.709
[ HUMMING ]

09:48.583 --> 09:52.333
♪ OOH, OOH, OOH, OOH, OOH ♪
[ FINGERS SNAPPING ]

09:52.417 --> 09:57.834
OOH, OOH, OOH, OOH ♪,

09:57.917 --> 10:02.333
♪ OOH, OOH, OOH, OOH,
OOH, OOH, OOH, OOH ♪

10:02.417 --> 10:03.709
WE CAN DO BETTER
THAN THAT.

10:03.792 --> 10:05.375
LET'S TRY THAT AGAIN.
OKAY.

10:05.458 --> 10:09.041
♪ OOH, OOH, OOH, OOH,
OOH, OOH, OOH, OOH ♪

10:09.125 --> 10:11.125
[ CELLPHONE RINGS ]

10:15.750 --> 10:17.041
OH. [ SIGHS ]

10:17.125 --> 10:21.166
CHARLIE, BABY,
IF THIS IS ABOUT YOU...

10:21.250 --> 10:23.125
I'M SORRY.

10:23.208 --> 10:26.583
<i>DON'T WORRY.</i>
<i>I TOTALLY GET IT.</i>

10:26.667 --> 10:28.583
HI, NURSE JACKSON. I JUST
WANTED TO GIVE YOU THE HEADS-UP

10:28.667 --> 10:32.083
THAT THE APPLE SAUCE IS ONE DAY
PAST ITS EXPIRATION DATE.

10:32.166 --> 10:34.250
UH, I'M SURE IT'S FINE.
I JUST WANTED TO DOUBLE-CHECK.

10:34.333 --> 10:36.417
OH, ALSO, WE ARE DOWN
TO OUR LAST BOX OF GLOVES,

10:36.500 --> 10:38.875
AND I CAN'T FIND THE KEY
TO THE SUPPLY CLOSET ANYWHERE.

10:38.959 --> 10:41.709
YOU DIDN'T ACCIDENTALLY, UM,
TAKE IT HOME WITH YOU, DID YOU?

10:41.792 --> 10:43.709
OKAY, WELL, UH...
CALL ME BACK WHEN YOU CAN.

10:43.792 --> 10:45.542
IT'S BRITTANY, BY THE WAY.
UM...

10:45.625 --> 10:46.959
OH, WE MISS YOU. OH.

10:48.291 --> 10:51.709
MISS YOU, TOO, UM...
BECAUSE MY SHIFT IS ALMOST OVER

10:51.792 --> 10:54.041
AND YOU'RE HEADED
INTO SURGERY.

10:54.125 --> 10:56.542
SO I WILL MISS YOU
WHEN I LEAVE.

10:56.625 --> 10:59.125
JUST KIDDING,
'CAUSE THAT'S WEIRD.

11:01.458 --> 11:04.458
HAVE A GOOD REST OF YOUR DAY,
BRITTANY.

11:06.917 --> 11:08.875
DID SHE PICK UP?
WHAT DID SHE SAY?
[ SIGHS ]

11:08.959 --> 11:11.125
STRAIGHT TO VOICEMAIL
AGAIN.

11:15.834 --> 11:18.291
Jay: YOU HAVE TO SEE
THE STADIUM AT UCLA.

11:18.375 --> 11:19.542
IT FEELS LIKE YOU'RE IN RIO
OR SOMETHING.

11:19.625 --> 11:20.792
THAT'S WHERE
WE'RE GONNA END UP.

11:20.875 --> 11:22.458
[ CHUCKLES ]
I DON'T KNOW.

11:22.542 --> 11:24.959
WHAT ABOUT YOU, LAUREN?
YOU SEE ANYPLACE YOU WANT TO GO?

11:25.041 --> 11:27.125
UH, I LIKED THE WOMEN'S STUDIES
DEPARTMENT AT BERKELEY.

11:27.208 --> 11:28.709
OH, YOU'RE THINKING
ABOUT BERKELEY?

11:28.792 --> 11:30.375
THAT'S ONE OF MY --
SAFETY SCHOOLS. YEAH.

11:30.458 --> 11:32.083
MINE TOO.
WHAT ARE YOUR TOP FIVE?

11:32.166 --> 11:34.959
HARVARD, YALE, PRINCETON...
YALE, PRINCETON, BROWN...

11:35.041 --> 11:36.417
...OBERLIN.
...BENNINGTON.

11:36.500 --> 11:38.208
[ CHUCKLES ]
I LIKE HER.

11:38.291 --> 11:41.417
ETHAN WANTS TO GO
TO OBERLIN.
WHO'S ETHAN?

11:41.500 --> 11:43.583
OH, JUST THIS GUY
I'M DATING --

11:43.667 --> 11:47.083
<i>WAS</i> DATING. ALTHOUGH ACTUALLY,
WE NEVER TECHNICALLY BROKE UP.

11:47.166 --> 11:50.166
Lauren: HE UNFRIENDED YOU
ON FACEBOOK.

11:50.250 --> 11:52.458
I'M SO DONE
TALKING ABOUT ETHAN.

11:52.542 --> 11:54.250
LET'S EAT.
I WANT EVERYTHING.

11:54.333 --> 11:57.250
EMMA,
WHAT ARE YOU HAVING?

11:57.333 --> 11:59.583
<i>FOUR WORDS</i>
<i>YOU NEVER SAY TO EMMA.</i>

11:59.667 --> 12:01.000
OH, I'M NOT HUNGRY.
[ LAUGHS ]

12:01.083 --> 12:04.625
SERIOUSLY?
WHAT'S WRONG WITH YOU?

12:04.709 --> 12:07.959
OH, MY GOD. I'M THE DEVIL.
I DON'T EVEN KNOW WHAT YOU HAVE.

12:08.041 --> 12:09.375
WHAT DO YOU HAVE?

12:09.458 --> 12:12.959
♪ SHE SUGAR SHAKES ♪

12:13.041 --> 12:20.625
I AM ACTUALLY IN THE HOSPITAL
BEING TREATED FOR ANOREXIA.

12:20.709 --> 12:23.750
SO, ARE YOU GUYS
READY TO ORDER?

12:23.834 --> 12:25.875
Jay: UM, ACTUALLY, WE'RE GONNA
CHECK OUT THE SPECIALS

12:25.959 --> 12:26.959
ON THE BOARD FIRST.

12:27.041 --> 12:30.917
BE RIGHT BACK.
[ SIGHS ]

12:31.041 --> 12:34.041
I THOUGHT YOU SAID
YOU TOLD THEM ABOUT ME.

12:34.125 --> 12:35.959
I DID -- JUST, YOU KNOW,
NOT WHY YOU'RE IN THE HOSPITAL.

12:36.041 --> 12:37.417
BECAUSE
IT'S EMBARRASSING?

12:37.500 --> 12:39.458
NO, 'CAUSE IT'S NOT MY PLACE
TO TELL.

12:39.542 --> 12:41.458
DID I DO
THE WRONG THING?

12:41.542 --> 12:43.709
NO. NO, YOU'RE RIGHT.

12:47.500 --> 12:50.166
[ BEEP, CLICK ]

12:59.166 --> 13:01.792
WAIT HERE.

13:01.875 --> 13:03.291
[ COUGHS ]

13:03.375 --> 13:05.417
TRY TO STAY QUIET.

13:05.500 --> 13:07.250
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

13:07.333 --> 13:10.250
[ BREATHES DEEPLY ]

13:10.333 --> 13:12.041
OH, SCREW THIS.

13:13.709 --> 13:16.250
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

13:19.250 --> 13:20.500
[ CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS ]

13:20.583 --> 13:21.792
I TOLD YOU TO STAY.

13:21.875 --> 13:24.333
YEAH, I'M NOT
A GOLDEN RETRIEVER.

13:24.417 --> 13:26.000
[ DOOR OPENS ]
WHY ARE YOU TAKING PICTURES
OF THE WALL?

13:26.083 --> 13:28.500
Shh, shh, shh.
Let's go.

13:28.583 --> 13:30.834
[ GASPS ]

13:30.917 --> 13:33.375
[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]

13:33.458 --> 13:35.375
Okay, enough with this
"What's real" crap.

13:35.458 --> 13:37.250
I want to know
what your real situation is.

13:37.333 --> 13:39.333
What happened
with your surgery?

13:39.417 --> 13:41.125
I didn't have
the surgery.

13:41.208 --> 13:43.667
Obviously. Why not?

13:45.375 --> 13:47.291
Come on. You can tell me.
I'm kind of known around here

13:47.375 --> 13:51.250
as someone
people can talk to.

13:55.458 --> 13:57.542
WHAT, AM I
IN "THE TWILIGHT ZONE"?

13:57.625 --> 13:59.125
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

13:59.208 --> 14:01.375
I'VE DECIDED I NO LONGER
WANT TO HAVE SEX WITH YOU...

14:01.458 --> 14:03.875
UNLESS <i>YOU</i> WANT TO,

14:03.959 --> 14:06.500
IN WHICH CASE
I CAN EASILY BE PERSUADED.

14:06.583 --> 14:08.125
DID YOU KNOW THAT

14:08.208 --> 14:09.834
WHEN THE NATIVE AMERICANS
OF THE PLAINS STATES

14:09.917 --> 14:12.750
WOULD KILL A BUFFALO,
THEY'D USE EVERY PART OF IT?

14:12.834 --> 14:15.083
WHAT?

14:15.166 --> 14:16.917
EVERY SINGLE PART.

14:17.000 --> 14:18.750
NOTHING COULD BE WASTED,

14:18.834 --> 14:21.250
UNLESS IT TURNED OUT
THE BUFFALO WAS SICK.

14:21.333 --> 14:24.417
THEN THEY'D JUST LEAVE IT
TO ROT IN THE SUN.

14:24.500 --> 14:27.834
OKAY, SURE.
I DON'T EAT RED MEAT, THOUGH.

14:27.917 --> 14:29.709
YOU EVER HEARD OF A GUY
NAMED DAVID ROSEN?

14:29.792 --> 14:32.417
I'M FROM BEVERLY HILLS.
I KNOW LIKE SEVEN DAVID ROSENS.

14:32.500 --> 14:35.250
THIS DAVID ROSEN
WAS A GREAT GUY, APPARENTLY --

14:35.333 --> 14:37.959
GREAT HUSBAND,
GREAT FATHER.

14:38.041 --> 14:40.709
BUT DAVID WASN'T QUITE READY
TO SETTLE INTO SUBURBAN LIFE.

14:40.792 --> 14:42.542
SO HE WENT OUT
AND BOUGHT A MOTORCYCLE.

14:42.625 --> 14:45.458
COUPLE DAYS AGO, HE CRASHED INTO
A SEMI ON THE FREEWAY AND DIED.

14:45.542 --> 14:49.291
IT TURNED OUT
THERE WAS ONE PERSON

14:49.375 --> 14:51.625
THAT COULD GIVE
DAVID'S DEATH SOME MEANING --

14:51.709 --> 14:54.792
A KID WITH
THE SAME RARE BLOOD TYPE

14:54.875 --> 14:56.875
WHO COULD REALLY USE
DAVID'S LIVER.

14:56.959 --> 14:59.500
EXCEPT WHEN THE SURGEON TOOK IT
OUT OF THE COOLER,

14:59.583 --> 15:01.959
HE SAW SOMETHING
NOBODY HAD NOTICED IN THE CAR

15:02.041 --> 15:05.291
OR THE PLANE
OR THE HELICOPTER.

15:05.375 --> 15:07.417
DAVID'S LIVER HAD A BIG,
BLACK SPOT ON IT.

15:07.500 --> 15:09.458
SO IT WENT IN THE TRASH,

15:09.542 --> 15:12.458
LIKE SOMETHING YOU'D FIND WAY
IN THE BACK OF THE FRIDGE.

15:12.542 --> 15:14.709
A ROTTEN BUFFALO.

15:14.792 --> 15:17.500
OH.

15:17.583 --> 15:19.208
YEAH.

15:19.291 --> 15:20.583
WAIT,
BUT WHAT HAPPENS

15:20.667 --> 15:22.667
IF THEY CAN'T FIND YOU
ANOTHER ONE?

15:24.667 --> 15:27.625
SAME THING
THAT HAPPENS TO YOU.

15:30.333 --> 15:33.041
♪ THERE WAS AN INVITATION ♪

15:34.417 --> 15:39.041
♪ TO TAKE PART
IN AN AWFUL SCENE ♪

15:39.125 --> 15:44.250
♪ AND YOU SAID THINGS
THAT WE COULD NOT BELIEVE ♪

15:44.333 --> 15:45.917
♪ THERE WAS A CELEBRATION ♪

15:46.000 --> 15:47.583
ARE YOU OKAY?

15:47.667 --> 15:49.250
♪ ONE THAT WE ALL WOULD NEED ♪
YEAH, I'M FINE.

15:49.333 --> 15:53.041
I'M SORRY. I ONLY ASK
'CAUSE I TRULY DON'T KNOW.

15:53.125 --> 15:56.291
I MEAN, LIKE,
WHEN YOU WATCH US EAT,

15:56.375 --> 16:01.083
DO YOU FEEL, LIKE,
HUNGRY OR...DISGUSTED?

16:01.166 --> 16:04.250
OR IS IT LIKE
A SMELL THING OR...?
YOU KNOW WHAT?

16:04.333 --> 16:07.041
I'M -- I'M PRETTY FULL.
ME TOO.
I THINK WE SHOULD GO.

16:07.125 --> 16:08.250
I MEAN,
IS IT MORE ABOUT CONTROL?

16:08.333 --> 16:10.333
OBVIOUSLY,
YOU'RE NOT ONE OF THOSE

16:10.417 --> 16:12.291
VAPID GIRLS
WHO READS FASHION MAGAZINES

16:12.375 --> 16:14.667
AND THINK YOU HAVE TO LOOK
LIKE SOME MODEL

16:14.750 --> 16:17.583
WHO WOULDN'T EVEN HAVE ORGANS
IF THAT WAS HER ACTUAL WAIST.

16:17.667 --> 16:19.250
LIKE...
CLEARLY YOU'RE SMART.

16:19.333 --> 16:23.417
INTELLECTUALLY, YOU MUST GET
THAT YOU'RE KILLING YOURSELF

16:23.500 --> 16:25.583
WITH THIS PASSIVE FORM
OF SLOW SUICIDE.

16:25.667 --> 16:28.875
SO...WHAT IS THIS ABOUT
FOR YOU?

16:28.959 --> 16:31.542
♪ AND AS THE ROAD GETS LONGER ♪

16:31.625 --> 16:35.875
♪ YOU WILL BE WALKING
ON YOUR OWN ♪
HONESTLY, UM...

16:35.959 --> 16:37.542
JUST BEING ABLE TO ADMIT

16:37.625 --> 16:39.709
THE FACT THAT I EVEN HAVE
A DISORDER OUT LOUD

16:39.792 --> 16:42.792
IS A HUGE DEAL FOR ME.

16:42.875 --> 16:46.125
TOTALLY. IT'S LIKE
WHEN I WAS FIRST COMING OUT.

16:46.208 --> 16:51.125
IT WAS SUCH A HUGE STEP JUST
TO SAY..."I'M GAY" OUT LOUD.

16:51.208 --> 16:54.333
SERIOUSLY? YOU'RE COMPARING
BEING GAY TO HAVING A DISEASE?

16:54.417 --> 16:55.917
NO. I'M JUST SAYING
THAT I UNDERSTAND --
YOU KNOW WHAT?

16:56.000 --> 16:58.166
SOMETIMES I THINK YOU AND ETHAN
DESERVE EACH OTHER.

16:58.250 --> 17:00.208
OKAY. I THOUGHT WE WERE "DONE"
TALKING ABOUT ETHAN.
YOU'RE RIGHT. WE ARE.

17:00.291 --> 17:03.917
WE ARE SO DONE TALKING ABOUT
ETHAN, TALKING ABOUT ANYTHING.

17:04.000 --> 17:06.166
WE NEED A NEW WORD FOR ETHAN.
I'M SO SORRY FOR HIM.

17:07.583 --> 17:11.417
[ COUGHING ]

17:11.500 --> 17:13.083
ARE YOU OKAY?

17:13.166 --> 17:15.083
WHAT DO YOU CARE?

17:15.166 --> 17:16.583
JUST 'CAUSE I DITCHED
MY RED BAND

17:16.667 --> 17:18.208
DOESN'T MEAN
WE'RE NOT FRIENDS, DASH.

17:18.291 --> 17:20.333
ACTUALLY,
IT KIND OF DOES.

17:20.417 --> 17:22.834
THOUGHT YOU WEREN'T GONNA LET
A GIRL MESS UP EVERYTHING.

17:22.917 --> 17:24.959
YEAH, AND YOU ALSO THOUGHT
MY MOM WAS GONNA STICK AROUND.

17:25.041 --> 17:26.291
SO I GUESS
WE WERE BOTH WRONG.

17:26.375 --> 17:30.250
LOOK, MAN,
I KNOW YOU'RE PISSED OFF,

17:30.333 --> 17:32.250
BUT BEING A PART OF RED BAND
MEANS SOMETHING.

17:32.333 --> 17:34.500
THE WAY I SEE IT,
WE'RE ALL WE GOT.

17:34.583 --> 17:37.166
SO AS LONG AS WE'RE IN IT
TOGETHER, WE'LL GET THROUGH IT.

17:37.250 --> 17:38.875
I KNOW
THAT'S THE WAY YOU SEE IT.

17:38.959 --> 17:40.458
BUT THE WAY I SEE IT,
I'M ALONE.

17:40.542 --> 17:42.041
THAT'S THE WAY
IT'S ALWAYS BEEN.

17:42.125 --> 17:43.583
AND WHEN
I FIRST GOT HERE,

17:43.667 --> 17:45.417
I THOUGHT MAYBE THINGS
COULD BE DIFFERENT,

17:45.500 --> 17:47.917
BUT THE LAST FEW DAYS MADE ME
REALIZE THAT I WAS WRONG.

17:49.834 --> 17:52.917
THE PROBLEM ISN'T THAT
I THREW AWAY MY RED BAND, DASH.

17:53.000 --> 17:54.917
THE PROBLEM IS THAT
I SHOULD HAVE NEVER PUT IT ON

17:55.000 --> 17:56.875
IN THE FIRST PLACE.

17:59.333 --> 18:01.959
YOU HAVE VISITORS.

18:02.041 --> 18:03.959
WHO DIED?
WE THOUGHT <i>YOU</i> DID.

18:04.041 --> 18:05.500
IT'S THE ONLY
LOGICAL EXPLANATION

18:05.583 --> 18:07.166
FOR NOT
RETURNING ANY OF OUR CALLS.

18:07.250 --> 18:09.041
OH, MY GOSH,
YOUR ROOM IS SO PRETTY!

18:09.125 --> 18:10.792
AND THAT KITCHEN --
AMAZE-BALLS.

18:10.875 --> 18:12.083
THOSE PEONIES
AND FRENCH ENAMELWARE --

18:12.166 --> 18:13.792
IT'S LIKE
YOU'RE LIVING MY DREAM.

18:13.875 --> 18:17.542
LUCKY ME. NOW,
WHAT ARE YOU TWO DOING HERE?

18:17.625 --> 18:20.375
WE CAME HERE TO TALK
SOME SENSE INTO YOU.
LOOK, YOU MADE A MISTAKE.

18:20.458 --> 18:22.041
<i>I</i> MADE A MISTAKE?
[ SCOFFS ]

18:22.125 --> 18:24.208
YES, <i>YOU</i> MADE A MISTAKE.
BUT YOU CAN FIX IT.

18:24.291 --> 18:26.917
ALL YOU HAVE TO DO IS APOLOGIZE
TO DR. McSTUPID.

18:27.000 --> 18:28.834
FOR WHAT?
GETTING CHARLIE A PERSONAL VISIT

18:28.917 --> 18:30.458
FROM THE BEST DOCTOR
IN THE WORLD?

18:30.542 --> 18:31.959
SORRY, <i>NOT</i> SORRY.

18:32.041 --> 18:34.125
OKAY, YOU MAY HAVE DONE IT
FOR THE RIGHT REASONS,

18:34.208 --> 18:36.792
BUT YOU HANDLED IT
ALL WRONG.
YOU KNOW WHAT'S WRONG?

18:36.875 --> 18:38.291
THE FACT THAT
I HAVE CLEANED UP EVERY SINGLE,

18:38.375 --> 18:39.458
SOLITARY MESS
THAT MAN HAS EVER MADE.

18:39.542 --> 18:40.959
AND FOR THE RECORD,

18:41.041 --> 18:43.041
HE HAS MADE MANY A MESS,
BUT WE WERE FRIENDS.

18:43.125 --> 18:45.375
AT LEAST I THOUGHT WE WERE
UNTIL HE WENT AND DID THIS.

18:45.458 --> 18:47.417
SO, YOU KNOW WHAT?
SCREW HIM.

18:47.500 --> 18:49.083
SCREW HIM.
SCREW THE WHOLE DAMN HOSPITAL.

18:49.166 --> 18:51.250
HELL, I DON'T OWE YOU PEOPLE
ANYTHING!

18:51.333 --> 18:55.500
I HAVE PLENTY OF OTHER THINGS
I CAN BE DOING WITH MY LIFE.

18:55.583 --> 18:58.250
IT'S TRUE. AUNT DENA WAS
A PROFESSIONAL BACKUP SINGER.

18:58.333 --> 19:01.125
KEYWORD -- "WAS."

19:01.208 --> 19:04.792
OH, I <i>KNOW</i>
YOU DIDN'T JUST SAY THAT.

19:04.875 --> 19:06.417
IT'S A MUSCLE, DENA.

19:06.500 --> 19:08.792
YOU GOT TO USE IT
OR YOU LOSE IT.

19:10.500 --> 19:12.583
SO YOU DON'T THINK
I CAN BRING IT?

19:12.667 --> 19:13.667
MM-HMM.

19:13.750 --> 19:15.959
OH.

19:16.041 --> 19:17.917
I THINK
YOU CAN BRING IT.

19:18.000 --> 19:20.792
MM-HMM.

19:23.792 --> 19:25.125
WATCH ME.

19:41.208 --> 19:43.208
STAY BACK.

19:45.125 --> 19:48.291
THIS IS IT.
THIS IS REAL.

19:48.375 --> 19:50.291
COME ON, MAN. SURGERY?
WE'VE ALL HAD SURGERY.

19:50.375 --> 19:52.333
YOU'VE ALL <i>HAD</i> IT,
BUT HAVE YOU EVER <i>SEEN</i> IT?

19:52.417 --> 19:55.834
NOTICE HOW THERE'S NO
BAND POSTERS ON THE WALLS,

19:55.917 --> 19:57.333
NOTHING TO MAKE US FEEL

19:57.417 --> 19:59.333
LIKE WE'RE JUST NORMAL KIDS
HANGING OUT AT HOME.

19:59.417 --> 20:01.166
BECAUSE
WE <i>AREN'T</i> NORMAL KIDS.

20:01.250 --> 20:02.834
THIS ISN'T HOME.

20:02.917 --> 20:04.500
WE'RE NOT HERE
TO FALL IN LOVE

20:04.583 --> 20:07.166
OR FORM SECRET SOCIETIES
THAT BAND TOGETHER

20:07.250 --> 20:09.125
AROUND A TOUGH NURSE
WITH A HEART OF GOLD.

20:09.208 --> 20:11.667
WE'RE HERE FOR ONE REASON
AND ONE REASON ONLY --

20:11.750 --> 20:14.000
TO END UP ON THAT TABLE.

20:14.083 --> 20:15.667
IT DOESN'T MATTER
HOW MANY PEOPLE YOU'VE GOT

20:15.750 --> 20:17.834
WAITING FOR YOU
IN THE RECOVERY ROOM.

20:17.917 --> 20:20.375
WHEN YOU'RE ON THAT TABLE,
YOU'RE ALONE.

20:20.458 --> 20:23.208
AND IF YOU DON'T GET OFF
THAT TABLE...

20:23.291 --> 20:25.875
YOU'RE ALONE FOR THAT,
TOO.

20:29.291 --> 20:32.291
NOW,
WHO WANTS TO LOOK FIRST?

20:34.709 --> 20:36.417
SO GOOD TO SEE YOU.

20:36.500 --> 20:38.041
LIKEWISE.

20:38.125 --> 20:39.542
[ P.A. BEEPS ]

20:39.625 --> 20:41.417
YOU TOO. THANKS FOR COMING,
GUYS. THANKS.

20:41.500 --> 20:43.291
HEY, LOOK FOR A PACKAGE
IN A WEEK OR TWO.

20:43.375 --> 20:45.250
I'M GONNA SEND YOU
A COPY OF EVERYTHING
THE RECRUITERS GIVE ME.

20:45.333 --> 20:47.291
AH, YOU DON'T
HAVE TO DO THAT.

20:47.375 --> 20:48.917
YEAH, I DO.
WE HAD A DEAL, LEO.

20:49.000 --> 20:51.500
I'M NOT LETTING
YOU WALK AWAY SO EASILY.

20:51.583 --> 20:53.291
UH, YOU THINK WALKING'S EASY?
[ CHUCKLES ]

20:54.667 --> 20:58.333
UM...YEAH, OKAY.
I'LL THINK ABOUT IT.

20:58.417 --> 21:00.917
FAIR ENOUGH. EMMA,
IT WAS A PLEASURE MEETING YOU.

21:01.000 --> 21:03.125
YEAH, YOU TOO.

21:06.500 --> 21:08.208
WELL,
SHE SEEMS...GREAT.

21:08.291 --> 21:10.291
YEAH. <i>SUPER</i> GREAT.

21:12.500 --> 21:15.083
[ CHUCKLES ]

21:15.166 --> 21:19.125
YEAH. SHE'S, UH...

21:19.208 --> 21:21.709
[ MONITOR BEEPING ]

21:21.792 --> 21:27.166
<i>THIS IS ONE OF THOSE RARE TIMES</i>
<i>I'M HAPPY TO BE IN A COMA.</i>

21:27.250 --> 21:30.333
<i>SERIOUSLY, WHO NEEDS TO SEE</i>
<i>ALL THAT BLOOD?</i>

21:30.417 --> 21:34.000
<i>UNLESS IT'S "GAME OF THRONES,"</i>
<i>I'M NOT INTERESTED.</i>

21:39.375 --> 21:42.041
[ THE BLACK ANGELS'
"TIRED EYES" PLAYS ]

21:42.125 --> 21:43.417
HE SAW ME!

21:43.500 --> 21:45.834
<i>UH-OH. BUSTED.</i>

21:48.625 --> 21:50.250
OH, MY GOD!
OTHER WAY, OTHER WAY!

21:50.333 --> 21:55.917
♪ PLEASE DON'T FALL OUT
OF LOVE ♪

21:57.375 --> 22:02.041
♪ YOU LEFT ME
AND MY WOODEN HEART ♪

22:04.917 --> 22:10.417
♪ CLAWED ME
WITH YOUR TIRED EYES ♪

22:13.417 --> 22:16.792
♪ YOU SET UPON THE NIGHT ♪

22:20.041 --> 22:23.583
GOING SOMEWHERE?

22:27.291 --> 22:32.542
♪ LET'S RIDE TO THE SUN,
ME AND YOU ♪

22:32.625 --> 22:37.792
♪ SO, LET'S FLY TO THE SUN,
JUST US TWO ♪

22:37.875 --> 22:39.875
[ SPARSE APPLAUSE ]

22:39.959 --> 22:43.166
WHOO! GREAT JOB,
PERSON I DON'T KNOW.

22:43.250 --> 22:45.500
THESE APPLE MARTINIS
ARE THE BOMB.

22:45.583 --> 22:48.291
IT'S YOUR TURN, AUNT DENA.
GIVE ME A MINUTE.

22:48.375 --> 22:51.333
I'M JUST SIPPING MY DRINK,
GETTING A LAY OF THE LAND.

22:51.417 --> 22:53.959
SHE <i>OBVIOUSLY</i>
DOESN'T WANT TO SING.

22:55.625 --> 22:57.166
Brittany: OH.

22:58.834 --> 23:01.166
OH, MY GOSH.

23:01.250 --> 23:02.750
OKAY, THIS IS GONNA BE
THE BEST VINE I EVER MADE.

23:02.834 --> 23:04.959
DO YOU HAVE SOME KIND
OF A DEATH WISH, MARY POPPINS?

23:07.625 --> 23:10.625
[ PIANO PLAYS
"MIDNIGHT TRAIN TO GEORGIA" ]

23:18.250 --> 23:20.583
♪ MM, L.A. ♪

23:22.583 --> 23:26.333
♪ PROVED TOO MUCH FOR THE MAN ♪

23:26.417 --> 23:28.875
[ MAN WHISTLES ]

23:28.959 --> 23:31.083
♪ SO HE'S LEAVING A LIFE ♪

23:34.250 --> 23:39.208
♪ HE'S COME TO KNOW ♪

23:39.291 --> 23:43.917
♪ HE SAID HE'S GOING BACK
TO FIND ♪

23:44.000 --> 23:48.792
♪ OOH-OOH,
WHAT'S LEFT OF HIS WORLD ♪

23:51.542 --> 23:53.959
♪ THE WORLD HE LEFT BEHIND ♪

23:54.041 --> 24:01.125
♪ NOT SO LONG AGO ♪

24:01.208 --> 24:05.291
♪ HE'S LEAVING ♪

24:05.375 --> 24:09.291
♪ ON THAT MIDNIGHT TRAIN
TO GEORGIA ♪

24:09.375 --> 24:12.125
♪ YEAH ♪

24:12.208 --> 24:14.959
♪ SAID HE'S GOING BACK ♪

24:16.750 --> 24:20.375
♪ TO A SIMPLER PLACE IN TIME ♪

24:20.458 --> 24:23.375
DAMN.
SHE'S STILL GOT IT.

24:23.458 --> 24:26.709
♪ AND I'LL BE WITH HIM ♪
TOLD YA.

24:26.792 --> 24:31.041
♪ ON THE MIDNIGHT TRAIN
TO GEORGIA ♪

24:31.125 --> 24:33.417
♪ YEAH, Y'ALL ♪

24:34.959 --> 24:37.709
♪ I'D RATHER LIVE IN HIS WORLD ♪

24:37.792 --> 24:42.875
♪ THAN LIVE WITHOUT HIM
IN MINE ♪

24:42.959 --> 24:44.834
[ APPLAUSE ]
Woman: OW!

24:52.583 --> 24:55.166
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

24:55.250 --> 24:57.709
DID YOU REALLY HAVE TO END
THE DAY LIKE THAT?

24:57.792 --> 24:59.458
OH, DID I EMBARRASS YOU?
I'M <i>SO</i> SORRY.

24:59.542 --> 25:01.875
MAYBE YOU MISSED THE PART
WHERE I WAS BEING WATERBOARDED

25:02.000 --> 25:03.875
WITH A GIANT VAT
OF MELTING SOUR CREAM.

25:03.959 --> 25:06.792
OKAY, LET'S TAKE
A SMALL REALITY CHECK.
ARE YOU KIDDING ME?

25:06.875 --> 25:09.208
THAT GIRL WAS ATTACKING ME.
OH, COME ON. SHE WASN'T.

25:09.291 --> 25:12.250
LOOK, I'M NOT GONNA PRETEND
LAUREN IS THE MOST TACTFUL
PERSON ON THE PLANET,

25:12.333 --> 25:14.333
BUT SHE WAS JUST
TRYING TO UNDERSTAND.

25:14.417 --> 25:16.000
AND WHAT WERE <i>YOU</i> DOING,
LEO?

25:16.083 --> 25:17.500
YOU DIDN'T EVEN
TRY TO DEFEND ME.

25:17.583 --> 25:22.417
'CAUSE I CAN'T.
I DON'T KNOW HOW.

25:22.500 --> 25:24.333
AND EVEN IF I DID, I WOULDN'T --
I WOULDN'T WANT TO.

25:24.417 --> 25:26.458
I DON'T KNOW
WHAT YOU'RE SAYING TO ME.

25:26.542 --> 25:27.959
I COULDN'T ARGUE
WITH LAUREN

25:28.041 --> 25:30.041
BECAUSE I AGREE
WITH EVERYTHING SHE SAID.

25:30.125 --> 25:32.041
I DON'T UNDERSTAND

25:32.125 --> 25:35.709
HOW SOMEONE SO...COOL
AND SMART AND BEAUTIFUL

25:35.792 --> 25:37.291
CAN DO THIS TO HERSELF.

25:37.375 --> 25:39.333
FINE! YOU OBVIOUSLY FEEL
LIKE YOU'VE MADE A MISTAKE.

25:39.417 --> 25:41.208
SO WHY DON'T WE JUST FORGET
THE WHOLE THING?

25:41.291 --> 25:43.875
EMMA, I'M NOT GOING ANYWHERE.
I JUST WANT TO...

25:44.000 --> 25:46.166
[ SIGHS ]
I WANT TO HELP YOU.

25:47.500 --> 25:51.417
I WANT US TO GET OUT OF HERE
TOGETHER.

25:53.709 --> 25:55.834
DON'T YOU WANT THAT?

26:00.834 --> 26:02.583
DON'T YOU?

26:02.667 --> 26:04.667
<i>THERE'S NOTHING WORSE</i>
<i>FOR A GUY WHO BEAT CANCER</i>

26:04.750 --> 26:08.333
<i>THAN TO COME UP AGAINST A FIGHT</i>
<i>HE CAN'T QUITE WIN.</i>

26:08.417 --> 26:10.291
DON'T YOU?

26:10.375 --> 26:11.959
[ P.A. BEEPS ]

26:12.041 --> 26:14.417
I DON'T KNOW.

26:33.709 --> 26:37.792
WHAT THE HELL
ARE YOU THINKING?
<i>I KNOW THIS SOUNDS CRAZY.</i>

26:37.875 --> 26:40.375
YOU GUYS SHOULD KNOW BETTER.
<i>BUT I KIND OF LOVE GETTING</i>
<i>YELLED AT LIKE THIS.</i>

26:40.458 --> 26:42.125
THESE RULES
ARE FOR YOUR OWN SAFETY.
<i>IT MAKES ME FEEL</i>
<i>LIKE PART OF THE GROUP.</i>

26:42.208 --> 26:43.875
YOU'RE SNEAKING
INTO A STERILE AREA.
WHAT'S GOING ON?

26:43.959 --> 26:45.709
THAT'S EXACTLY WHAT I'M TRYING
TO FIGURE OUT RIGHT NOW.

26:45.792 --> 26:47.041
WHY? WHAT HAPPENED?

26:47.125 --> 26:48.583
YOU LEFT!
THAT'S WHAT HAPPENED!

26:48.667 --> 26:50.417
AND NO ONE
WANTED TO LISTEN TO ME.

26:50.500 --> 26:51.959
HOW DID YOU EVEN GET
UP THERE?

26:52.041 --> 26:52.750
I'LL TELL YOU
EXACTLY HOW WE GOT UP THERE.

26:52.834 --> 26:54.625
[ COUGHS ]

26:54.709 --> 26:57.375
WE GOT UP THERE BECAUSE THERE
WAS NO ONE HERE TO STOP US.

26:57.458 --> 26:58.875
IT'S LIKE "LORD OF THE FLIES"
IN HERE, MAN --

26:58.959 --> 27:01.375
NO SOLIDARITY,
EVERY MAN FOR THEMSELVES.

27:01.458 --> 27:05.291
NURSE JACKSON --
[ COUGHS ]

27:05.375 --> 27:07.667
NURSE JACKSON IS THE ONE WHO
HELD THIS WHOLE THING TOGETHER,

27:07.750 --> 27:10.458
BUT YOU FIRED HER.
DASH, I DIDN'T FIRE
NURSE JACKSON.

27:10.542 --> 27:12.250
OH, SUSPENDED,
WHATEVER YOU WANT TO CALL IT.

27:12.333 --> 27:15.291
FOR WHAT? BECAUSE -- BECAUSE SHE
TRIED TO SAVE CHARLIE'S LIFE?

27:15.375 --> 27:18.959
[ COUGHS ]
DASH, TRY TO STAY CALM.

27:19.041 --> 27:21.166
YOU DON'T EVEN CARE ABOUT THAT,
DO YOU? [ COUGHS ]

27:21.250 --> 27:23.625
YOU THINK YOU'RE THE ONLY ONE
IN HERE SAVING PEOPLE, MAN?

27:23.709 --> 27:25.458
[ COUGHS ]
DASH, TAKE IT EASY. BREATHE.

27:25.542 --> 27:26.875
[ COUGHS, SPITS ]

27:26.959 --> 27:28.333
OH, MY GOD!
OKAY, OKAY.

27:28.417 --> 27:30.500
Leo: DASH!
NURSE, WE NEED A GURNEY.

27:30.583 --> 27:32.291
WHAT'S HAPPENING?
IT'S OKAY.
HE'S GONNA BE ALL RIGHT.

27:32.375 --> 27:34.125
I JUST NEED SOME ROOM HERE.
ALL RIGHT, HERE WE GO.

27:34.208 --> 27:36.250
GRAB HIS HEAD.
ON THE COUNT OF THREE, GUYS.

27:36.333 --> 27:39.542
1, 2, 3. UP.

27:39.625 --> 27:42.208
OKAY. OKAY,
THERE YOU GO, BUD.

27:42.291 --> 27:43.458
TAKE A QUICK LISTEN.

27:43.542 --> 27:47.166
ALL GOOD, ALL GOOD.

27:47.250 --> 27:49.834
[ CELLPHONE RINGS ]

27:52.417 --> 27:55.333
EMMA, HI.

27:55.417 --> 27:58.250
HEY. I THOUGHT
YOU GUYS WERE GONE.

27:58.333 --> 28:00.041
OH, I LEFT MY PHONE
IN THE BATHROOM.

28:00.125 --> 28:02.500
THEY SHOULD REALLY
ISSUE WARNINGS ABOUT
TEXTING AND PEEING.

28:02.583 --> 28:04.041
[ CHUCKLES ]
I'M GLAD I RAN INTO YOU.

28:04.125 --> 28:07.250
I WANTED TO APOLOGIZE
ABOUT THIS AFTERNOON.

28:07.333 --> 28:09.375
OH, IT'S NOT YOUR FAULT.
IT'S JUST KIND OF EMBARRASSING.

28:09.458 --> 28:11.041
I MEAN, EVERYBODY HAS
SOMETHING ABOUT THEMSELVES
THEY DON'T LIKE.

28:11.125 --> 28:13.166
FOR EXAMPLE, I CAN'T KEEP
MY MOUTH SHUT TO SAVE MY LIFE.

28:13.250 --> 28:15.000
OH, YOU DON'T SAY?
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

28:15.083 --> 28:18.500
WELL, SINCE YOU ALREADY KNOW
I HAVE ABSOLUTELY NO FILTER,

28:18.583 --> 28:21.041
LET ME JUST SAY THIS.

28:21.125 --> 28:23.792
LEO IS SERIOUSLY
THE MOST AMAZING GUY EVER.

28:23.875 --> 28:26.542
I KNOW.
NO, I MEAN, HE REALLY IS.

28:26.625 --> 28:29.709
AND NOT JUST BECAUSE HE'S...
A GREAT ATHLETE

28:29.792 --> 28:31.417
OR SMART OR CUTE,

28:31.500 --> 28:36.083
BUT BECAUSE HE'S TRULY,
PROFOUNDLY GOOD.

28:36.166 --> 28:37.500
DO YOU KNOW WHAT I MEAN?

28:37.583 --> 28:39.500
I THINK SO.
BUT HE'S NOT A SAINT.

28:39.583 --> 28:42.166
I MEAN,
HE MIGHT THINK HE IS, BUT...

28:42.250 --> 28:44.834
WHATEVER HE SAYS, HE'S NOT GONNA
WAIT AROUND FOREVER

28:44.917 --> 28:46.500
FOR YOU TO GET YOUR ACT
TOGETHER.

28:46.583 --> 28:48.500
HE'LL TRY,
BUT SOONER OR LATER,

28:48.583 --> 28:51.500
IF YOU KEEP THIS UP,
YOU'RE GONNA LOSE HIM.

28:51.583 --> 28:54.083
BY BEING MYSELF?

28:54.166 --> 28:57.583
IN THE NICEST POSSIBLE WAY,
YEAH.

28:57.667 --> 28:59.583
[ ELEVATOR BELL DINGS ]
SO GET BETTER, OKAY?

28:59.667 --> 29:01.750
<i>WHEN YOU'RE IN THE HOSPITAL,</i>

29:01.834 --> 29:04.083
<i>PEOPLE ARE ALWAYS TELLING YOU</i>
<i>IT'S GONNA BE OKAY,</i>

29:04.166 --> 29:06.083
<i>SO WHAT DO YOU DO</i>
<i>WHEN SOMEONE TELLS YOU</i>

29:06.166 --> 29:09.709
<i>YOUR GREATEST FEAR</i>
<i>MIGHT ACTUALLY COME TRUE?</i>

29:09.792 --> 29:11.834
I CANNOT GET OVER
HOW TALENTED YOU ARE.

29:11.917 --> 29:15.208
I WOULD KILL TO HAVE A TALENT
LIKE THAT...OR ANY TALENT.

29:15.291 --> 29:17.041
OH, DON'T BE SO HARD
ON YOURSELF.

29:17.125 --> 29:18.667
YOU HAVE
A GREAT SENSE OF COLOR,

29:18.750 --> 29:20.458
AND YOU'RE VERY GOOD
AT NAMING STUFFED ANIMALS.

29:20.542 --> 29:22.125
I MEAN,
I JUST DON'T GET IT, DENA.

29:22.208 --> 29:24.000
MAY I CALL YOU DENA?
YOU MAY NOT.

29:24.083 --> 29:27.000
HOW COULD YOU EVER GIVE THAT UP?
WHAT HAPPENED?

29:29.542 --> 29:31.125
LIFE HAPPENED.

29:31.208 --> 29:33.792
♪ OOH, OOH, OOH, OOH,
OOH, OOH, OOH, OOH ♪

29:33.875 --> 29:36.041
[ LAUGHTER ]

29:36.125 --> 29:38.375
LAVERNE, BABY, YOU WERE FLATTER
THAN A BLUEBERRY PANCAKE.

29:38.458 --> 29:39.834
MM.
COME ON.
ONE MORE TIME.

29:39.917 --> 29:41.500
LET'S SHOW HER HOW IT'S DONE.
COME ON.

29:41.583 --> 29:42.875
♪ OOH, OOH, OOH, OOH,
OOH, OOH, OOH, OOH ♪

29:42.959 --> 29:44.417
DENA, THERE'S A PHONE CALL
FOR YOU.

29:44.500 --> 29:45.750
CAN IT WAIT?
I MEAN, WE'RE ABOUT TO GO ON.

29:45.834 --> 29:48.500
IT'S FROM THE HOSPITAL.

29:56.875 --> 29:59.125
EXCUSE ME.
Doctor: DENA?

29:59.208 --> 30:03.000
WHERE'S MY SISTER?

30:03.083 --> 30:06.709
WHY DON'T
WE STEP OUTSIDE?

30:08.875 --> 30:11.959
[ SIGHS ]
IT WAS VERY PEACEFUL.

30:12.041 --> 30:14.542
SHE'S STILL IN HER ROOM.
HER HUSBAND IS WITH HER NOW.

30:14.625 --> 30:16.125
HE ASKED
FOR SOME TIME ALONE.

30:16.208 --> 30:18.959
I WAS IN REHEARSALS
ALL DAY.

30:19.041 --> 30:22.792
I WAS PLANNING TO COME
FIRST THING IN THE MORNING.

30:22.875 --> 30:24.959
[ MONITOR BEEPING ]

30:25.041 --> 30:28.625
[ Voice breaking ]
I DIDN'T GET TO SAY GOODBYE.

30:28.709 --> 30:29.750
[ BREATHES SHAKILY ]

30:34.083 --> 30:37.166
Woman:
<i>DR. FORREST, DIAL 182, PLEASE.</i>

30:37.250 --> 30:39.458
HEY, CUPCAKE.

30:39.542 --> 30:42.792
MOMMY'S REALLY SICK
THIS TIME.

30:42.875 --> 30:45.333
SHE ISN'T GONNA
GET BETTER.

30:45.417 --> 30:47.000
I KNOW, BABY.

30:47.083 --> 30:49.667
[ ELEVATOR BELL DINGS ]

30:49.750 --> 30:52.500
BUT AUNT DENA'S HERE.

30:52.583 --> 30:55.250
OKAY?

30:58.583 --> 31:01.834
THAT WAS THE END OF
MY GLAMOROUS LIFE ON THE ROAD.

31:01.917 --> 31:06.333
MY ONLY SISTER WAS GONE,
MY BROTHER-IN-LAW DEVASTATED,

31:06.417 --> 31:10.500
AND MY LITTLE SABRA --
SHE NEEDED ME.

31:10.583 --> 31:14.667
<i>NEEDED.</i> PAST TENSE.

31:14.750 --> 31:17.041
I'M ALL GROWN UP NOW,

31:17.125 --> 31:19.500
AND YOU COULD HAVE IT ALL BACK
IF YOU WANT.

31:19.583 --> 31:21.500
SHE'S RIGHT.
YOU COULD, AND YOU SHOULD.

31:21.583 --> 31:24.291
YOU SO SHOULD.
Kenji: NO, SHE SHOULDN'T.

31:24.375 --> 31:27.000
WHY DO YOU THINK SHE BECAME
A NURSE IN THE FIRST PLACE?

31:27.083 --> 31:28.959
UM, WELL,
SHE JUST TOLD US.

31:29.041 --> 31:31.125
NO, SHE TOLD US
WHY SHE STOPPED SINGING.

31:31.208 --> 31:34.208
THAT'S NOT WHY SHE CHOSE
TO BECOME A NURSE.

31:34.291 --> 31:36.208
YOU COULD HAVE DONE
A MILLION THINGS

31:36.291 --> 31:37.792
THAT KEPT YOU CLOSE
TO YOUR FAMILY,

31:37.875 --> 31:40.667
BUT YOU CHOSE NURSING
BECAUSE YOU LOVE KIDS.

31:40.750 --> 31:42.458
YOU DO.

31:42.542 --> 31:44.875
THE WAY YOU TOOK CARE OF SABRA,
THE WAY YOU PROPPED UP

31:44.959 --> 31:46.667
HER DAD WHEN THE BOTTOM
HAD FALLEN OUT OF HIS LIFE

31:46.750 --> 31:48.500
AND HE COULD BARELY
GET OUT OF BED.

31:48.583 --> 31:52.500
THAT'S WHAT YOU DO FOR JORDI
AND DASH AND LEO...

31:52.583 --> 31:53.792
AND CHARLIE.

31:55.375 --> 31:58.625
YOU'RE THERE FOR PEOPLE
WHEN THEY NEED YOU MOST,

31:58.709 --> 32:00.709
AND THAT'S WHY
IT'S YOUR CALLING.

32:02.125 --> 32:05.917
[ CELLPHONE RINGS ]

32:07.625 --> 32:11.041
YES?

32:11.125 --> 32:12.917
I'M ON MY WAY.

32:14.166 --> 32:16.000
GET HER HOME.

32:16.083 --> 32:18.166
AND HER, TOO.

32:18.250 --> 32:20.834
IT LOOKS LIKE
SHE GOT ANOTHER CALLING.

32:20.917 --> 32:23.458
I'M VERY DRUNK.

32:23.542 --> 32:25.542
[ TELEPHONE RINGS ]

32:31.959 --> 32:33.709
WHAT ARE YOU
DOING HERE?

32:33.792 --> 32:36.208
JUST GRABBING MY BOOK.
HOW'S YOUR FRIEND?

32:36.291 --> 32:39.041
THEY DIDN'T PULL THE PLUG
ON HIM YET, DID THEY?

32:39.125 --> 32:40.375
[ P.A. BEEPS ]
[ SCOFFS ]

32:40.458 --> 32:42.000
YOU KNOW WHAT, HUNTER?

32:42.083 --> 32:44.625
EVEN FOR A NIHILIST,
YOU'RE A REAL SACK OF CRAP.

32:44.709 --> 32:46.792
I NEVER SAID
I WAS A NIHILIST.
RIGHT.

32:46.875 --> 32:49.083
'CAUSE WHAT KIND OF NIHILIST
NEEDS AN AUDIENCE?

32:49.166 --> 32:51.917
LOOK, NONE OF YOU GUYS
HAD TO COME WITH ME TODAY.

32:52.000 --> 32:53.458
YOU MADE
YOUR OWN CHOICE.

32:53.542 --> 32:56.792
HEY, I'M GLAD I CAME.
I LEARNED A LOT.

32:56.875 --> 32:58.792
AND, YOU KNOW,
YOU'RE RIGHT.

32:58.875 --> 33:01.500
THIS IS
ALL A DISTRACTION.

33:01.583 --> 33:03.792
AND YOU DON'T NEED TO BE
ONE OF US.

33:03.875 --> 33:08.000
BUT WHEN <i>YOU</i> FALL,
WE'RE GONNA BE THERE ANYWAYS.

33:08.083 --> 33:11.667
MAYBE WE DO
ALL DIE ALONE,

33:11.750 --> 33:14.875
BUT THAT DOESN'T MEAN
WE NEED TO LIVE ALONE.

33:14.959 --> 33:16.542
[ FOOTSTEPS DEPART ]

33:16.625 --> 33:18.917
[ P.A. BEEPS ]

33:20.750 --> 33:23.667
[ BALL THUDDING ]

33:23.750 --> 33:26.250
[ TELEPHONE RINGS ]

33:30.834 --> 33:32.083
CAN YOU CUT THAT OUT?

33:32.166 --> 33:33.583
[ P.A. BEEPS ]

33:36.458 --> 33:39.208
HE'S STABLE. AND AT THIS POINT,
HE JUST NEEDS TO REST.

33:39.291 --> 33:40.875
IT'S BECAUSE OF TODAY,
ISN'T IT?

33:40.959 --> 33:42.291
I SHOULDN'T HAVE
LET HIM COME WITH US.

33:42.375 --> 33:43.417
I KNEW HE WAS
HAVING TROUBLE KEEPING UP.

33:43.500 --> 33:44.750
HIS RESPIRATORY THERAPIST

33:44.834 --> 33:46.667
SAID HE MISSED
TWO TREATMENTS TODAY.

33:46.750 --> 33:49.125
WHAT THE HELL WERE YOU DOING
UP THERE?
I DON'T KNOW.

33:49.208 --> 33:50.959
WE DIDN'T EVEN KNOW
WHERE WE WERE GOING AT FIRST,

33:51.041 --> 33:52.333
BUT ONCE WE WERE THERE...

33:53.208 --> 33:54.834
LOOK, WE JUST WANTED TO SEE
WHAT IT WAS REALLY LIKE.

33:54.917 --> 33:56.792
Charlie: <i>AND THAT'S WHEN</i>
<i>DR. McANDREW REALIZED</i>

33:56.875 --> 34:00.291
<i>SOMETIMES YOU DON'T BREAK</i>
<i>THE RULES BECAUSE YOU'RE ANGRY.</i>

34:00.375 --> 34:02.959
<i>SOMETIMES YOU BREAK THE RULES</i>
<i>BECAUSE YOU'RE SCARED.</i>

34:03.041 --> 34:05.000
THEY GAVE HIM A SEDATIVE
SO HE CAN REST EASIER.

34:05.083 --> 34:06.500
NOW YOU GUYS CAN GO
TO YOUR ROOM.

34:06.583 --> 34:08.083
I'LL STAY.
NO, I'LL STAY.

34:08.166 --> 34:10.667
ONLY ONE OF YOU WILL STAY.

34:10.750 --> 34:12.667
WORK IT OUT.

34:12.750 --> 34:15.959
Woman:
<i>DR. FLORENCE, DIAL 182, PLEASE.</i>

34:16.041 --> 34:17.458
[ SIGHS ]

34:17.542 --> 34:19.291
THE OTHER DAY,
I SHOULDN'T HAVE HIT YOU, MAN.

34:19.375 --> 34:21.792
IT'S OKAY.
NO, IT'S NOT.

34:24.667 --> 34:27.750
[ SIGHS ]
LOOK, YOU TAKE THE FIRST SHIFT,

34:27.834 --> 34:29.875
TEXT ME WHEN YOU GET TIRED,
AND I'LL COME BACK.

34:29.959 --> 34:32.208
SOUNDS GOOD.

34:32.291 --> 34:34.333
[ CHUCKLES ]

34:41.166 --> 34:43.166
[ TELEPHONE RINGS ]

34:45.709 --> 34:48.709
I'M NOT HERE TO FIGHT.

34:48.792 --> 34:50.959
GREAT.
I'M TOO TIRED TO FIGHT.

34:51.041 --> 34:52.875
BUT I'M ALSO
NOT GOING TO APOLOGIZE.

34:52.959 --> 34:56.834
ME, NEITHER.

34:56.917 --> 34:58.500
[ SIGHS ]

34:58.583 --> 34:59.917
I'M GLAD I GOT TO MEET
YOUR FRIENDS.

35:00.000 --> 35:02.125
I REALLY LIKE THEM.

35:02.208 --> 35:04.250
THEY'RE THE KIND OF PEOPLE THAT
I'D WANT TO BE FRIENDS WITH,

35:04.333 --> 35:07.083
YOU KNOW,
IF I HAD FRIENDS THAT WAY.

35:07.166 --> 35:09.041
YOU DO, AND YOU WILL.

35:10.208 --> 35:14.166
[ SIGHS ]

35:14.250 --> 35:15.792
I MEANT TO TELL YOU,

35:15.875 --> 35:17.000
MY DAD MIGHT BE COMING UP
TO VISIT NEXT WEEK.

35:17.083 --> 35:18.917
AND I DON'T KNOW
IF IT'S TOO SOON,

35:19.000 --> 35:21.625
BUT I'D REALLY LIKE FOR YOU
TO MEET HIM, IF YOU WANT.

35:21.709 --> 35:24.625
I'D LOVE TO.

35:27.333 --> 35:28.667
[ SIGHS ]

35:31.417 --> 35:33.667
ARE THOSE THE ONES WITH
THE MARSHMALLOW IN THE MIDDLE?

35:33.750 --> 35:35.000
THEY'RE FINALLY
IN SEASON.

35:38.709 --> 35:42.125
THOSE USED TO BE MY FAVORITE
WHEN I WAS LITTLE.

35:42.208 --> 35:43.333
CAN I HAVE ONE?

35:44.959 --> 35:48.542
REALLY?

35:48.625 --> 35:50.917
HELP YOURSELF.

36:02.542 --> 36:05.333
♪ YOU WILL NEVER KNOW YOU LIKE
I KNOW YOU, LIKE I KNOW YOU ♪
HOW'S IT TASTE?

36:05.417 --> 36:07.333
♪ AND I'LL START ♪
LIKE HOME.

36:07.417 --> 36:10.792
♪ I COULD SHOW YOU
HOW YOU'RE LOVELY ♪

36:10.875 --> 36:13.125
MY MOUTH IS FULL.
I DON'T CARE.

36:13.208 --> 36:15.959
♪ TAKE THESE THINGS IN STRIDE ♪

36:16.041 --> 36:20.959
♪ AND LET YOUR HEART BE WIDE ♪

36:21.041 --> 36:25.792
♪ IF NO ONE EVER GOES ♪

36:25.875 --> 36:29.959
♪ THEN NO ONE EVER GROWS ♪

36:30.041 --> 36:32.917
IT'S SO CHOCOLATY.

36:34.458 --> 36:38.500
I KNOW. I KNOW I'M NOT
SUPPOSED TO BE HERE.
YOU'RE NOT.

36:38.583 --> 36:40.500
LISA CALLED,
SAID IT WAS AN EMERGENCY,

36:40.583 --> 36:42.166
SAID SOMETHING ABOUT DASH?

36:42.250 --> 36:46.417
DASH IS FINE. HE HAD AN EVENT,
BUT HE'S BACK TO BASELINE.

36:46.500 --> 36:47.750
GOOD.

36:47.834 --> 36:49.500
MM-HMM.

36:49.583 --> 36:52.000
THAT'S GOOD.

36:52.083 --> 36:53.834
<i>DR. STEIN, DIAL THE OPERATOR,</i>
<i>PLEASE.</i>

36:53.917 --> 36:56.625
<i>DR. STEIN, DIAL THE OPERATOR,</i>
<i>PLEASE.</i>
UH...

36:57.875 --> 37:01.750
THAT'S...ALL, I GUESS.

37:03.542 --> 37:07.583
KENJI CAN CLEAN OUT THE REST
OF MY DESK IN THE MORNING.

37:07.667 --> 37:09.959
DENA,
I TOLD LISA TO CALL YOU.

37:11.667 --> 37:13.250
YOU DID?

37:13.333 --> 37:16.542
I UNDERSTAND WHY YOU DID
WHAT YOU DID.

37:16.625 --> 37:20.250
BUT YOU CANNOT AFFORD
TO TAKE THOSE TYPES OF RISKS.

37:20.333 --> 37:22.250
A-AND I CAN APPRECIATE
THAT.

37:22.333 --> 37:24.750
I-I-I THOUGHT
ABOUT EVERYTHING THAT HAPPENED,

37:24.834 --> 37:29.709
AND...YOU MAY NOT HAVE BEEN
COMPLETELY WRONG.

37:29.792 --> 37:32.500
WHICH MEANS THAT YOU MAY NOT
HAVE BEEN COMPLETELY RIGHT.

37:32.583 --> 37:35.625
IT GOES TO FOLLOW.

37:35.709 --> 37:38.750
I'M GUESSING THAT'S AS CLOSE
TO AN APOLOGY AS I'M GONNA GET.

37:38.834 --> 37:41.750
TAKE IT OR LEAVE IT.
[ ELEVATOR BELL DINGS ]

37:41.834 --> 37:44.250
I'LL TAKE IT.

37:44.333 --> 37:47.417
ALL RIGHT, THEN.

37:47.500 --> 37:50.875
I'LL SEE YOU WHEN MY SUSPENSION
IS LIFTED.

37:50.959 --> 37:52.959
I'VE LIFTED
YOUR SUSPENSION.

37:55.500 --> 37:59.583
I REALIZE THAT THESE KIDS MEAN
EVERYTHING TO YOU,

37:59.667 --> 38:04.333
BUT WHAT I DIDN'T KNOW IS
HOW MUCH YOU MEAN TO THESE KIDS.

38:04.417 --> 38:07.500
THEY NEED YOU,

38:07.583 --> 38:12.208
AND, MORE IMPORTANTLY,
I NEED YOU.

38:12.291 --> 38:16.834
THEN I GUESS
I'M WHERE I NEED TO BE.

38:16.917 --> 38:19.625
[ INDISTINCT TALKING OVER P.A. ]

38:19.709 --> 38:22.542
[ IMAGINE DRAGONS'
"I BET MY LIFE" PLAYS ]

38:25.083 --> 38:27.417
[ SIGHS ]

38:38.500 --> 38:43.250
♪ I'VE TOLD A MILLION LIES,
BUT NOW I TELL A SINGLE TRUTH ♪

38:43.333 --> 38:47.083
♪ THERE'S YOU
IN EVERYTHING I DO ♪

38:47.166 --> 38:48.917
♪ NOW,
REMEMBER WHEN I TOLD YOU ♪

38:49.000 --> 38:51.583
♪ THAT'S THE LAST
YOU'LL SEE OF ME ♪

38:51.667 --> 38:53.542
♪ REMEMBER WHEN I BROKE YOU DOWN
TO TEARS ♪

38:53.625 --> 38:55.375
Dash:
"'TO WHOM IT MAY CONCERN' --

38:55.458 --> 38:57.583
"THAT'S THE CORRECT WAY
TO ADDRESS SOMEBODY

38:57.667 --> 39:00.291
"WHEN YOU HAVE NO IDEA
WHO THEY ARE.

39:00.375 --> 39:01.792
Jordi: "BUT MAYBE THAT
DOESN'T MATTER SO MUCH,

39:01.875 --> 39:05.000
"BECAUSE THIS LETTER IS
REALLY ABOUT WHO WE ARE.

39:05.083 --> 39:06.500
Leo: "ARISTOTLE SAID
THAT KNOWING YOURSELF

39:06.583 --> 39:08.166
"IS THE BEGINNING OF WISDOM.

39:08.250 --> 39:10.667
"WELL, HERE'S WHAT WE KNOW
SO FAR.

39:10.750 --> 39:13.500
WE'RE PEOPLE WHO ARE COMING TO
TERMS WITH WHO WE USED TO BE."

39:13.583 --> 39:15.500
Emma: "AND TRYING TO FIGURE OUT
WHERE WE'RE GOING

39:15.583 --> 39:18.375
AND WHO WE'RE GOING THERE
WITH -- SORRY, 'WHOM.'"

39:18.458 --> 39:20.208
Kara:
"WHICH BRINGS US TO THE POINT

39:20.291 --> 39:23.125
OF THIS EMBARRASSINGLY EARNEST
LETTER -- NURSE JACKSON."

39:23.208 --> 39:24.667
♪ REMEMBER WHEN I TOLD YOU ♪

39:24.750 --> 39:26.959
♪ THAT'S THE LAST
YOU'LL SEE OF ME ♪

39:27.041 --> 39:28.625
Kara:
"I'M THE FIRST TO ADMIT

39:28.709 --> 39:30.709
"THAT NURSE JACKSON CAN BE
A PAIN IN THE ASS.

39:30.792 --> 39:34.000
"SHE'S BOSSY, INSULTING,

39:34.083 --> 39:37.667
AND HER TASTE IN FOOTWEAR
IS HIGHLY QUESTIONABLE."

39:37.750 --> 39:40.709
♪ THROUGH ALL THE YEARS ♪

39:40.792 --> 39:45.834
Kara:
"BUT THE TRUTH IS, WE NEED HER.

39:45.917 --> 39:47.834
AND THOUGH SHE MAY NOT ADMIT
IT..."

39:47.917 --> 39:51.083
Charlie: <i>"SHE NEEDS US.</i>

39:51.166 --> 39:53.041
<i>"SO PLEASE LET HER COME BACK,</i>

39:53.125 --> 39:54.917
<i>"BECAUSE IF THERE'S ONE THING</i>
<i>WE'VE DEFINITELY LEARNED</i>

39:55.000 --> 39:57.917
<i>"ABOUT OURSELVES IN OUR LIMITED</i>
<i>TIME ON THIS EARTH</i>

39:58.000 --> 40:01.250
<i>IT'S THAT YOU HAVE TO KNOW</i>
<i>WHEN ENOUGH IS ENOUGH."</i>

40:01.333 --> 40:04.667
"SINCERELY,
THE RED BAND SOCIETY."

40:14.750 --> 40:16.250
Dash: CHARLIE?

40:30.333 --> 40:32.667
CHARLIE?

40:36.458 --> 40:39.291
CHARLIE, MAN, YOU HERE?

40:47.417 --> 40:50.083
CHARLIE?

40:51.917 --> 40:54.333
[ P.A. BEEPS ]

40:54.417 --> 40:57.417
CHARLIE, HONEY, IT'S ME.

41:00.875 --> 41:02.917
CHARLIE?

